"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-explainer-olympics-how-france-plans-to-use-ai-to-keep-paris-2024-safe\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  A view shows a surveillance camera as French police start to test artificial intelligence-assisted video surveillance of crowds in the run-up to the Olympics in Paris, France, March 6, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.999999839810711, \"rank\": 1.6018923357789975e-07, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.739307671168115e-31, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996216502, \"rank\": 3.7823768756707857e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Abdul Saboor    PublishedMar 08, 2024, 07:06 PM  UpdatedMar 08, 2024, 07:43 PM  PARIS - France tested Artificial Intelligence-driven video surveillance technology that will be deployed during the Olympic Games at a Depeche Mode concert this week, calling the exercise a success.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French legislation passed in 2023 permits the use of AI video surveillance for a trial period covering the Games to detect abnormal events or human behaviour at large-scale events.\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8251309150701409, \"rank\": 0.20750005985859915, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 771, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2223850069292373e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The technology could be pivotal to thwarting an attack like the bombing at the 1996 Olympics in Atlanta or the Nice truck attack in 2016, officials say.\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 996, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.999999999699412, \"rank\": 2.9970914063010296e-10, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 0.9999997812610911, \"rank\": 2.1870044796751907e-07, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rights campaigners warn the technology poses a threat to civil liberties.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT IS AI-POWERED SURVEILLANCE?\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Algorithmic video surveillance uses computer software to analyse images captured by video surveillance cameras in real time.\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four companies -- Videtics, Orange Business, ChapsVision and Wintics -- have developed AI software that use algorithms to analyse video streams coming from existing video surveillance systems to help identify potential threats in public spaces.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"score\": 0.9999999998067324, \"rank\": 1.931720919381633e-10, \"text\": \"Orange\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2223850069292373e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The algorithms are trained to detect pre-determined \\\"events\\\" and abnormal behaviour and send alerts accordingly.\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Human beings then decide if the alert is real and whether to act on it.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHAT WILL THE ALGORITHMS BE LOOKING FOR?\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The law allows for eight different \\\"events\\\" to be flagged by AI surveillance software during the Games that include: crowd surges; abnormally heavy crowds; abandoned objects; presence or use of weapons; a person on the ground; a fire breaking out; contravention of rules on traffic direction.\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2223850069292373e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within these categories, specific thresholds (number of people, type of vehicle, timing etc) can be set manually to cater for each individual event, location or threat.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WHO WILL USE AI-POWERED SURVEILLANCE?\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"National and local police, firefighters, public transport security agents will all have access to AI-powered surveillance.\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Software developed by Wintics and tested at the Depeche Mode concert, will be deployed in the Paris region and on public transport.\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996216502, \"rank\": 3.7823768756707857e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Police chief Laurent Nunez described the trial as largely a success.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996216502, \"rank\": 3.7823768756707857e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everything went relatively well, all the lights are green (for future use),\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WILL FACIAL RECOGNITION BE USED?\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should not.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new law continues to ban facial recognition in most cases and French authorities have said it is a red line not to be crossed.\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8251309150701409, \"rank\": 0.20750005985859915, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, rights campaigners are concerned mission creep risks setting in down the line.\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Software that enables AI-powered video surveillance can easily enable facial recognition.\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's simply a configuration choice,\\\" said Katia Roux of Amnesty International France.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3094, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"score\": 0.9999999907245183, \"rank\": 9.275695122632006e-09, \"text\": \"Katia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\"}, {\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1243370930011012e-12, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}, {\"begin\": 3130, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legal framework regulating facial recognition remained too fuzzy and technical and legal safeguards were insufficient, according to Amnesty International.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3275, \"end\": 3296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1243370930011012e-12, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wintics Co-founder Matthias Houllier said his software's algorithms were not trained for facial recognition.\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3318, \"end\": 3326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"score\": 0.9928929403076393, \"rank\": 0.006459358356763161, \"text\": \"Matthias\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no personal identification method in our algorithms,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's technically excluded.\\\"\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3510, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"HOW WILL PRIVACY BE PROTECTED?\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Interior Ministry has created an evaluation committee to keep tabs on civil liberties throughout the trial period.\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9837607056783388, \"rank\": 0.016507362235323644, \"text\": \"Interior Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Led by a high ranking official within France's top administrative court, the committee also comprises the head of the country's privacy watchdog, CNIL, four lawmakers and a mayor.\", \"from\": 3669, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3707, \"end\": 3713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3815, \"end\": 3819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commission_nationale_de_l'informatique_et_des_libert\\u00e9s\", \"score\": 0.9176265664961462, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CNIL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commission_nationale_de_l'informatique_et_des_libert\\u00e9s\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commission_nationale_de_l'informatique_et_des_libert\\u00e9s\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Surveillance  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 3995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3849, \"end\": 3856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3872, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9991906665866568, \"rank\": 0.0004628706251213083, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3912, \"end\": 3920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4029, \"entities\": []}]}"